quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,153,"O you who believe, seek help in patience and prayer, for Allah is with those who are patient"
  2,154,"And do not say that those martyred in Allah’s way are dead. Rather, they are alive, but you do not perceive it"
  2,155,"We will surely test you with something of fear and famine, and loss of property, lives and fruits. But give glad tidings to those who are patient"
  2,156,"Those when afflicted with a disaster, they say, “We belong to Allah, and to Him we will return.”"
  2,157,"They are those upon whom are blessings and mercy from their Lord, and it is they who are guided"
  2,158,"Indeed, Safa and Marwah [mounts] are among the symbols of Allah. So whoever performs the pilgrimage or ‘Umra, there is no blame upon him to go between them. And whoever does good voluntarily, then Allah is All-Appreciative, All-Knowing"
  2,159,Those who conceal the clear proofs and guidance that We have sent down – after We explained it clearly for people in the Scripture – it is they who are cursed by Allah and will be cursed by those who curse
  2,160,"Except for those who repent, mend their deeds, and clarify the truth; I will surely accept their repentance, for I am the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,161,"Those who disbelieve and die as disbelievers are cursed by Allah and the angels, and by all people"
  2,162,"They will abide in [the curse] forever. Their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be granted any respite"
  2,163,"And your god is one God. None has the right to be worshiped except Him – the Most Compassionate, the Most Merciful"